Package: mbp-cirrus-audio-dkms
Version: 1.0-1
Section: kernel
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: dkms (>= 2.2.0.3), build-essential, patch, wget
Recommends: linux-headers-generic | linux-headers-amd64
Maintainer: Vinicius Fontanela <[email protected]>
Description: Cirrus CS8409 HDA audio driver (DKMS) for T2-era MacBook Pro/iMac
 Out-of-tree DKMS package providing the snd-hda-codec-cs8409 kernel
 module needed for internal speaker/microphone audio on Macs with the
 Cirrus Logic CS8409 HDA codec + MAX98706/SSM3515 amplifiers (most
 2017+ MacBook Pro and iMac Pro models with a T2 chip).
 .
 This is a repackaging, as DKMS source, of davidjo/snd_hda_macbookpro
 (github.com/davidjo/snd_hda_macbookpro), with the dkms.conf fix from
 that project's issue #164 (CFLAGS_MODULE overrides needed to build
 cleanly on GCC 14+ / kernel 6.17+, which also covers kernel 7.x).
 .
 IMPORTANT: at build time (both at install and at every future kernel
 update) this driver's PRE_BUILD step downloads the sound/hda subtree
 of a kernel source tree matching your *exact* running kernel version -
 either via the distro's linux-source-<version> package (Ubuntu/
 Debian) or from kernel.org directly. This requires:
   - internet access at the time DKMS (re)builds the module
   - a linux-source-<version> package that actually matches your
     running kernel (does NOT work with Ubuntu HWE kernels - see
     docs/TROUBLESHOOTING.md in the source repo)
 If either of those isn't satisfied, the (re)build will fail and audio
 will stay broken until you install the matching linux-source package
 and re-run dkms manually - see the package's docs for exact commands.
 .
 To reduce this, the bundled install script caches the patched kernel
 source tree per kernel version under /var/cache/mbp-cirrus-audio-dkms/,
 so routine Ubuntu kernel ABI bumps (which share the same underlying
 kernel version) rebuild fully offline. Only a genuine new upstream
 kernel version still needs a fresh download.
